WEBVTT

00:05.130 --> 00:05.839
<i>[lively music]</i>

00:07.298 --> 00:09.175
Hey, Sherm.
You see that girl back there?

00:09.175 --> 00:10.635
The girl at the jukebox?

00:10.635 --> 00:12.095
- Oh, yeah, she's cute.
- All right.

00:12.095 --> 00:13.388
So I'm coming back
from the bathroom.

00:13.388 --> 00:15.223
I hear her going on and on
and on about boxing.

00:15.223 --> 00:17.100
I figure you go over there,
talk to her about boxing,

00:17.100 --> 00:18.435
you probably have a shot.

00:18.435 --> 00:21.021
Ooh, that's
what I'm talking 'bout, Nicky.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.188
Thanks for looking out.

00:22.188 --> 00:24.691
Now y'all prepare
to watch a master...

00:24.691 --> 00:25.734
at work.

00:25.734 --> 00:27.694
[laughter]

00:27.694 --> 00:29.362
Get it.
Get it.

00:29.362 --> 00:31.156
I made all of that up.
This is a prank.

00:31.156 --> 00:32.449
She wasn't talking
about boxing.

00:32.449 --> 00:33.867
- Amazing.
- Oh.

00:33.867 --> 00:35.869
This is gonna be a disaster,
and I love it.

00:35.869 --> 00:36.953
Oh, it's starting.

00:36.953 --> 00:38.371
Oh, there he goes.

00:38.371 --> 00:39.664
This is even better
than I thought it would be.

00:39.664 --> 00:41.249
He's actually
pretending to box.

00:41.249 --> 00:42.417
I don't understand.

00:42.417 --> 00:43.710
Did he tell her
that he's a boxer?

00:43.710 --> 00:45.962
- Wow, wow, wow, wow.
- What is he doing?

00:45.962 --> 00:47.213
Good little combo.

00:47.213 --> 00:48.757
- Oh, he got hit.
- He took a shot?

00:48.757 --> 00:49.924
- Kind of a stick and move.
- Okay.

00:49.924 --> 00:51.217
He's doing "The Matrix" now.

00:51.217 --> 00:52.844
- Oh, she don't like it?
- Oh, she stopped him.

00:52.844 --> 00:54.387
- She's telling him something.
- She told him to leave.

00:54.387 --> 00:55.889
She's saying,
"I don't like violence."

00:55.889 --> 00:57.140
Oh, no.

00:57.140 --> 00:58.558
Oh, we got him good.

01:00.643 --> 01:02.562
That could not
have gone better.

01:02.562 --> 01:04.189
We're headed back
to her place.

01:04.189 --> 01:06.608
- Thank you, Nicky.
- Yeah.

01:08.151 --> 01:09.903
- I--
- I just--

01:09.903 --> 01:10.945
<i>♪ Whoop, whoop ♪</i>

01:10.945 --> 01:12.280
<i>♪ Cabernet and sauvignon ♪</i>

01:12.280 --> 01:13.907
<i>♪ Team is here
and now it's on ♪</i>

01:13.907 --> 01:16.868
<i>♪ Carry on and Carignan,
sippin' on Perignon ♪</i>

01:16.868 --> 01:18.620
<i>♪ Fine wine,
got notes like a cello ♪</i>

01:18.620 --> 01:19.871
<i>♪ Pull up in the spot
like hello ♪</i>

01:19.871 --> 01:21.539
<i>♪ If you got me,
then I got you ♪</i>

01:21.539 --> 01:23.333
<i>♪ This is the vibe,
this is the crew ♪</i>

01:23.333 --> 01:25.835
<i>♪ Grand crew, grand crew, uh ♪</i>

01:25.835 --> 01:28.463
<i>♪ Grand crew, grand crew,
grand crew, uh ♪</i>

01:28.463 --> 01:29.798
<i>♪ Grand crew ♪</i>

01:29.798 --> 01:31.633
Hey, you know
what I just realized?

01:31.633 --> 01:34.469
Everyone here is
in a relationship.

01:34.469 --> 01:36.596
Excuse you.
I ain't in no relationship.

01:36.596 --> 01:38.598
But you do say
you're married to the game.

01:38.598 --> 01:39.599
That's true.

01:39.599 --> 01:40.934
I am
in a long-term relationship

01:40.934 --> 01:42.268
with these streets.

01:42.268 --> 01:43.478
Well,
Kristen and I are hosting

01:43.478 --> 01:44.896
a little potluck next week.

01:44.896 --> 01:46.690
Plus-ones are welcome,
and if you guys are in,

01:46.690 --> 01:47.774
just text me
what you're bringing.

01:47.774 --> 01:49.109
Oh, I don't think
Michael is gonna

01:49.109 --> 01:50.276
make it to the potluck.

01:50.276 --> 01:52.195
He's in San Diego
for Uncle Phil Con.

01:52.195 --> 01:54.072
Uncle Phil Con?
Is that where--

01:54.072 --> 01:55.365
People who look
like Uncle Phil

01:55.365 --> 01:57.117
all hang out together
in a conference room?

01:57.117 --> 01:58.451
Yeah, uh-huh.

01:58.451 --> 01:59.911
He's always trying
to get me to go,

01:59.911 --> 02:01.371
and I don't know why.

02:01.371 --> 02:03.123
So how are things going
with my brother, Nicky?

02:03.123 --> 02:04.332
It's great.

02:04.332 --> 02:05.375
I only have to pay
for half the things,

02:05.375 --> 02:07.252
like hotels, meals,

02:07.252 --> 02:09.421
a box full
of old "Jet" magazines

02:09.421 --> 02:11.089
we stumbled upon
at a yard sale.

02:11.089 --> 02:12.966
Ooh, nice,
eight-year-old Sherm

02:12.966 --> 02:14.843
used to live for page 42.

02:14.843 --> 02:16.428
[chuckles]
Naughty.

02:16.428 --> 02:17.721
That's facts.

02:17.721 --> 02:18.763
Must be nice,

02:18.763 --> 02:20.306
dating someone
who is not married.

02:20.306 --> 02:21.891
Oh, no,
are things not working out

02:21.891 --> 02:23.935
between you
and your girlfriend's husband?

02:23.935 --> 02:25.478
Okay, let me just say
that I respect

02:25.478 --> 02:26.771
Courtney and Simone
being best friends.

02:26.771 --> 02:28.815
He did us a huge favor
by agreeing to marry her.

02:28.815 --> 02:31.609
So obviously, you know,
I'm very, very appreciative--

02:31.609 --> 02:33.319
CliffsNotes, my guy.
What happened?

02:33.319 --> 02:35.613
Okay, I don't like him,
he's mean, and he sucks.

02:35.613 --> 02:37.657
This is such great weather
for a walk.

02:37.657 --> 02:39.576
Yeah, the sun
is really shining.

02:39.576 --> 02:42.537
Yeah.
That's what the sun does.

02:42.537 --> 02:45.707
- And then I was like, "Jenga!"
- Oh, my God.

02:45.707 --> 02:47.834
- [both laugh]
- That's the end of the story?

02:47.834 --> 02:49.002
That's cool.

02:49.002 --> 02:51.796
[forced laughter]

02:51.796 --> 02:53.506
I'm just, ugh, so tired

02:53.506 --> 02:55.300
of him being involved
in our relationship.

02:55.300 --> 02:56.384
And now,
with this immigration stuff,

02:56.384 --> 02:57.510
I have to deal
with him for months.

02:57.510 --> 02:58.803
Ooh, Kristen and I
are friends

02:58.803 --> 03:00.263
with this great
immigration lawyer.

03:00.263 --> 03:01.514
They can expedite
the whole process,

03:01.514 --> 03:02.849
get it done in a couple weeks.

03:02.849 --> 03:05.894
- Yes, please, thank you.
- Good.

03:05.894 --> 03:07.771
Don't let your girlfriend's
husband block your blessings.

03:07.771 --> 03:10.023
Mm-hmm.

03:10.023 --> 03:13.318
<i>[gentle music]</i>

03:13.318 --> 03:15.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:15.028 --> 03:17.655
- Aye.
- Aye.

03:17.655 --> 03:19.908
- Brush it.
- Brush it.

03:19.908 --> 03:21.534
Now freeze.

03:21.534 --> 03:22.702
♪ Who's brushing tonight? ♪

03:22.702 --> 03:23.953
both:
♪ Who's brushing tonight? ♪

03:23.953 --> 03:25.497
Now spit.

03:27.999 --> 03:29.376
[phone buzzes]

03:30.960 --> 03:32.462
That dresser drawer
I cleared out for you

03:32.462 --> 03:33.755
is really coming in handy,
I see.

03:33.755 --> 03:34.881
It is.

03:34.881 --> 03:36.257
I can't believe
you gave me the top one.

03:36.257 --> 03:38.802
Oh, welcome
to the good life, baby.

03:39.469 --> 03:42.055
It's almost like
we're moving in together.

03:42.055 --> 03:44.015
Yep, true.

03:44.015 --> 03:46.768
Uh-oh, I didn't mean
to make you uncomfortable.

03:46.768 --> 03:48.269
No, you didn't
make me uncomfortable.

03:48.269 --> 03:50.397
[laughs]
Babe, come on.

03:50.397 --> 03:51.981
You have
the worst poker face ever.

03:51.981 --> 03:53.566
You've been like this
as long as I've known you.

03:53.566 --> 03:55.068
Like you know me.

03:55.068 --> 03:57.112
Okay, so what do you think

03:57.112 --> 03:59.239
about my friend Tonya?

03:59.239 --> 04:01.825
- She's cool.
- Anthony.

04:01.825 --> 04:04.202
I just don't think she's
as young as she says she is.

04:04.202 --> 04:06.830
Why does she drink
so much Ovaltine?

04:06.830 --> 04:08.873
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:08.873 --> 04:10.875
<i>Thank you all
for meeting me here today.</i>

04:10.875 --> 04:12.627
I wanted to gather
my richest friends,

04:12.627 --> 04:14.921
and Wyatt,
to see if they'd be interested

04:14.921 --> 04:16.798
in getting in one the ground
floor of my newest venture.

04:16.798 --> 04:18.925
I need 90% equity
and complete creative control.

04:18.925 --> 04:21.261
I'm not interested
unless I get naming rights.

04:21.261 --> 04:23.179
- I'm sorry, I'm out.
- I ain't even pitched it yet.

04:23.179 --> 04:24.514
Damn!

04:24.514 --> 04:25.974
I've been dabbling
in a little winemaking,

04:25.974 --> 04:27.559
and I finally finished
my first batch.

04:27.559 --> 04:31.104
So I'd like to present to you
Jones & Sons Peach Wine,

04:31.104 --> 04:33.064
established 1776.

04:33.064 --> 04:35.108
I thought that the driving
business was your thing.

04:35.108 --> 04:36.484
Oh, I'm still doing that,

04:36.484 --> 04:38.403
but a mogul understands diversification.

04:38.403 --> 04:39.779
I don't know.

04:39.779 --> 04:42.157
The wine and spirits market
is really crowded.

04:42.157 --> 04:44.743
Even T.D. Jakes has a wine now.

04:44.743 --> 04:46.411
Can you just try it, please?
Please, please, please?

04:46.411 --> 04:47.620
- both: Okay.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

04:47.620 --> 04:49.330
- Yeah, yes.
- All right.

04:50.623 --> 04:52.542
- For you, Nicky.
- Thank you.

04:52.542 --> 04:54.169
- Wyatt.
- Oh.

04:54.169 --> 04:55.837
Kristen.

04:55.837 --> 04:58.298
- All right, all right.
- Hmm...

04:58.298 --> 05:01.009
<i>[pensive music]</i>

05:01.009 --> 05:03.094
Wow.

05:03.094 --> 05:04.304
This is amazing.

05:04.304 --> 05:05.805
It really is.

05:05.805 --> 05:08.099
Sherm, when you came out today,

05:08.099 --> 05:10.143
I was expecting the worst,

05:10.143 --> 05:11.644
but you've impressed me.

05:11.644 --> 05:12.645
- Same.
- Us too.

05:12.645 --> 05:14.105
[chuckles] Great!

05:14.105 --> 05:16.149
Let's start the bidding
at $10 million.

05:16.149 --> 05:17.359
<i>- ¿Escúchame?</i>
- Boy, what's wrong with you?

05:17.359 --> 05:18.568
I don't know
how much money y'all got.

05:18.568 --> 05:20.195
I was taking a shot.

05:20.195 --> 05:24.991
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:24.991 --> 05:27.035
So this is Wyatt's guy?

05:27.035 --> 05:28.036
Oh, no, no, no, no.

05:28.036 --> 05:29.245
He would've been
way too expensive.

05:29.245 --> 05:30.497
But this guy seems legit.

05:30.497 --> 05:31.664
- Saw him on a bus bench.
- Hmm.

05:31.664 --> 05:33.667
Dang, did we have
to do this so early?

05:33.667 --> 05:34.959
- It's 3:00 p.m.
- Oh, for real?

05:34.959 --> 05:36.961
That's late.
Why didn't we do this earlier?

05:36.961 --> 05:38.380
Well, this was
the only appointment

05:38.380 --> 05:39.673
we could get
at such short notice.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.216
[toilet flushing]
[door clicks]

05:41.216 --> 05:42.467
Greetings.

05:42.467 --> 05:44.511
I'm Carl Kurm
of Kurm & Associates.

05:44.511 --> 05:46.096
Little bit about me:

05:46.096 --> 05:48.223
I used to live in New York,
and I worked as a DA.

05:48.223 --> 05:49.641
Then a couple of months ago,

05:49.641 --> 05:51.685
I looked in the mirror,
and I said to myself,

05:51.685 --> 05:54.229
I need to switch some things up
before I turn 30.

05:54.229 --> 05:55.980
You're under 30?

05:55.980 --> 05:57.857
Yeah, I'm 27.

05:59.025 --> 06:01.695
Right, so me
and my husband were hoping

06:01.695 --> 06:03.905
to get me citizenship sooner
rather than later.

06:03.905 --> 06:04.989
Mm.

06:04.989 --> 06:07.117
How do you fit
into this situation?

06:07.117 --> 06:08.535
Oh, I'm her best friend.

06:08.535 --> 06:10.036
That checks out.

06:10.036 --> 06:12.372
Anyway, I have a buddy
who works for immigration.

06:12.372 --> 06:14.374
- Let me make a phone call.
- Okay.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.376
Really?
Wow, okay.

06:16.376 --> 06:17.627
Well, thanks a lot, buddy.

06:17.627 --> 06:18.753
All right, bye.

06:18.753 --> 06:20.338
That did not go well.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.215
Turns out,
he and I are not friends

06:22.215 --> 06:25.135
and you guys have been added
to the USCIS watchlist.

06:25.135 --> 06:26.970
- That's my bad.
- Wait, what does that mean?

06:26.970 --> 06:29.514
That means that ICE may show
up at your home at any moment

06:29.514 --> 06:31.307
to check that
your marriage is legitimate.

06:31.307 --> 06:32.684
And what happens
if we're not living together

06:32.684 --> 06:33.977
when ICE shows up?

06:33.977 --> 06:36.062
Well, I believe
the legal term is

06:36.062 --> 06:38.481
"instant deportation."

06:38.481 --> 06:42.277
Cool, so you two
will be living together.

06:42.277 --> 06:43.570
That's excellent.

06:43.570 --> 06:44.779
You're
a very supportive friend.

06:51.453 --> 06:52.370
Well,
the lawyer plan backfired.

06:53.580 --> 06:55.123
Simone and Courtney
are on a watchlist now,

06:55.123 --> 06:57.542
so they have to move in
together indefinitely.

06:57.542 --> 06:58.460
That doesn't sound
like something

06:58.460 --> 06:59.794
my lawyer friend would do.

06:59.794 --> 07:01.212
Yeah, your lawyer friend
was too expensive.

07:01.212 --> 07:02.714
I went with a bus ad attorney.

07:02.714 --> 07:04.883
Everyone knows
you can't trust a bus ad.

07:04.883 --> 07:06.634
Unless it's real estate, right?

07:06.634 --> 07:08.970
My ads.
They look good, right?

07:08.970 --> 07:10.930
Right?

07:10.930 --> 07:12.307
[bleep] all y'all!

07:12.307 --> 07:14.559
So, uh, check this.

07:14.559 --> 07:15.935
Talia and I were hanging out
the other night,

07:15.935 --> 07:17.604
and she sort of
kind of mentioned

07:17.604 --> 07:18.938
the idea of us
moving in together.

07:18.938 --> 07:21.316
- That's exciting.
- Yeah, it's dope.

07:21.316 --> 07:22.484
- Oh.
- Mm-mm.

07:22.484 --> 07:23.485
- Oh, wow.
- What?

07:23.485 --> 07:24.778
I said it's... dope.

07:24.778 --> 07:26.488
Oh, honey,
we heard what you said.

07:26.488 --> 07:27.655
We just know you're lying.

07:27.655 --> 07:29.366
You have no poker face.

07:29.366 --> 07:31.451
Wait, so everybody
knows this about me?

07:31.451 --> 07:33.578
You've been like this
since forever.

07:33.578 --> 07:34.954
<i>Like the time
Sherm came to visit</i>

07:34.954 --> 07:36.790
<i>and I introduced you guys
at UCLA.</i>

07:36.790 --> 07:39.167
Hey, man, it was real nice
to meet you, bro.

07:39.167 --> 07:40.794
Uh, yeah. Cool.

07:40.794 --> 07:43.296
It was nice to meet you too.

07:43.296 --> 07:44.881
What the hell?
You didn't like me?

07:44.881 --> 07:46.675
I liked you.
I always liked you.

07:46.675 --> 07:48.510
- You're doing it right now.
- Damn.

07:48.510 --> 07:50.178
My stupid face
always snitching on me.

07:50.178 --> 07:52.138
Wait, how did you leave
that discussion with Talia?

07:52.138 --> 07:54.599
Kind of open-ended?

07:54.599 --> 07:56.643
I know, I know.
I should bring it up again.

07:56.643 --> 07:58.728
But, you know, I'm just not
sure how I feel about it.

07:58.728 --> 07:59.854
You should count
your blessings!

07:59.854 --> 08:02.524
Count every single one,
you damn fool!

08:02.524 --> 08:04.359
- Whoa.
- Sorry.

08:04.359 --> 08:05.944
I just wish I had what you had.

08:05.944 --> 08:10.198
My girlfriend's moving in with
her fake husband, who I hate.

08:10.198 --> 08:12.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:12.951 --> 08:14.953
Yo, Amir,
would you ever be interested

08:14.953 --> 08:16.371
in serving a new wine
here at the bar?

08:16.371 --> 08:18.331
Sure, man.
What you got?

08:18.331 --> 08:20.583
Ooh, Jones & Sons.

08:20.583 --> 08:22.335
Very nice.
I like this.

08:22.335 --> 08:24.629
Wait.
Did you make this at home?

08:24.629 --> 08:26.923
Oh, yes, sir.
Crafted from the finest grapes.

08:26.923 --> 08:29.634
Found in the produce aisle
at my local Food 4 Less.

08:29.634 --> 08:32.554
Well, that's exciting,
but I can't sell this wine.

08:32.554 --> 08:33.680
- Why not?
- Licensing.

08:33.680 --> 08:35.015
Regulation issues.

08:35.015 --> 08:36.891
Not to mention,
the serious risk of botulism.

08:36.891 --> 08:39.227
Botulism?
Botch, please.

08:39.227 --> 08:41.229
[chuckles]
What is botulism?

08:41.229 --> 08:43.815
Botulism is
an awful bacterial disease.

08:43.815 --> 08:46.276
It can cause symptoms
like difficulty breathing,

08:46.276 --> 08:48.570
paralysis,
oftentimes death.

08:48.570 --> 08:51.531
- I've seen it tear people up.
- Whew.

08:51.531 --> 08:53.450
It's actually not a problem
at all if you cleaned the jugs.

08:53.450 --> 08:56.119
[chuckles]
Oh, I cleaned the jugs.

08:56.119 --> 08:58.288
<i>Oh, no.
I did not clean the jugs.</i>

08:58.288 --> 09:01.916
Hey, for educational purposes,
'cause I love knowledge,

09:01.916 --> 09:04.252
uh, if someone were
to not clean the jugs

09:04.252 --> 09:06.087
and then serve this
to a group of friends,

09:06.087 --> 09:07.881
how long would it be
until I knew they were safe?

09:07.881 --> 09:10.091
Well, symptoms can appear
anytime up to ten days.

09:10.091 --> 09:12.177
Oh, okay,
well, it's a good thing

09:12.177 --> 09:14.387
we ain't got to worry
about that, right?

09:14.387 --> 09:15.597
<i>Oh, no.
I am so worried.</i>

09:15.597 --> 09:17.307
<i>I might have poisoned
my friends!</i>

09:17.307 --> 09:19.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:19.809 --> 09:22.312
All right.
Well, this is my place.

09:22.312 --> 09:23.438
Simone, make yourself at home.

09:23.438 --> 09:24.522
Noah, thank you for grabbing

09:24.522 --> 09:25.690
the smallest bag
you could find.

09:25.690 --> 09:26.941
It had heavy stuff in it.

09:26.941 --> 09:28.818
Mm, the stuff
was heavy for you.

09:28.818 --> 09:31.029
- I'm taller than you are.
- Bro, that's mostly hair.

09:31.029 --> 09:32.822
- You're, like, 5'7".
- Oh, I'm tall-tall.

09:32.822 --> 09:34.115
I'll shave my head off
right now, boy.

09:34.115 --> 09:35.533
Okay, that's enough.

09:35.533 --> 09:37.452
You guys obviously
don't like each other.

09:37.452 --> 09:38.870
That's not true.

09:38.870 --> 09:40.622
I have no issue with Courtney,
except for the fact

09:40.622 --> 09:42.207
that he's the coldest person
I've ever met.

09:42.207 --> 09:43.416
Why are you in my home?
I don't even know you, man.

09:43.416 --> 09:44.793
See?

09:44.793 --> 09:46.252
Okay, well,
we're finally communicating.

09:46.252 --> 09:49.464
And you both want me to stay
in the country, don't you?

09:49.464 --> 09:50.799
- both: Yeah.
- See?

09:50.799 --> 09:52.550
That's already one thing
you have in common.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.177
And there's bound to be more.

09:54.177 --> 09:55.553
So I'm thinking

09:55.553 --> 09:57.806
you should spend
